Fix pod sync with missing historical LFS

Allow automatic pod-to-host pushes to continue when Git LFS cannot
find old objects that were already absent from both the pod and host.

This keeps pod branches syncing while still uploading LFS objects that
are introduced by the pod before the Git ref moves, then skips Git LFS'
whole-branch pre-push scan for that internal ref push. It adds
regressions for a non-LFS pod commit on top of history with a missing
old LFS payload, and for a new pod-created LFS pointer whose payload is
missing locally.
